section.section:
The provisions of this subsection do not apply to the following counties:
Baltimore;
Carroll;
Frederick;
Howard;
Prince George's, except as to paragraph (3) of this subsection; and
Worcester.

For an applicant to obtain a license under this subsection:
The applicant shall apply in the regular manner and pay the usual fee; and
The restaurants for which the licenses are sought shall:
Meet the requirements of the rules and regulations of the Board of License Commissioners regarding the availability and issuance of licenses;
Meet the definition requirements of "restaurant" established under the regulations of the Board of License Commissioners;
Have a minimum seating capacity of 190 persons for dining;
Have a cocktail lounge or bar area seating capacity that does not exceed 25% of the seating capacity for dining; and
Have no more than 40% of sales in alcoholic beverages in connection with the business.

An indirect interest is presumed to exist between two individuals, corporations, limited liability companies, partnerships, limited partnerships, joint ventures, associations, or other combination of persons, if they:
Have a common parent company;
Are parties to a franchise agreement, licensing agreement, or concession agreement;
Are part of a chain of businesses that is commonly owned and operated;
Share a director, stockholder, partner, or member;
Share a director, stockholder, partner, or member of a parent or subsidiary;
Share, directly or indirectly, profit from the sale of alcoholic beverages; or
Share a trade name, trademark, logo or theme, or mode of operation identifiable by the public.

Notwithstanding any other provision of this section or § 8-204(l) of this article, in Baltimore County, an individual or a sole proprietorship, partnership, corporation, unincorporated association, or limited liability company in the county, may obtain a direct or indirect interest in not more than 13 Class B (on-sale - hotels and restaurants) beer, wine and liquor licenses under this article, by making application in the regular manner and paying the usual fee if the restaurant for which the additional license is sought:
Meets the requirements of the rules and regulations of the Board of License Commissioners regarding the availability and issuance of licenses;
Meets the definition requirements of "restaurant" established under the regulations of the Board of License Commissioners;
Has a cocktail lounge or bar area seating capacity that does not exceed 25% of the seating capacity for dining;
Has no more than 40% of sales in alcoholic beverages in connection with the business; and
Is located in the Liberty Road Commercial Revitalization District as defined by the County Council on October 18, 1999.

For purposes of this subsection, an indirect interest is presumed to exist between two persons, corporations, limited liability companies, partnerships, limited partnerships, joint ventures, associations, or other combination of persons, whether natural or otherwise, if any of the following conditions exist between them:
A common parent company;
A franchise agreement;
A licensing agreement;
A concession agreement;
Both are part of a chain of businesses commonly owned and operated;
They share:
Directors, stockholders, partners, or members; or
Directors, stockholders, partners, or members of parents or subsidiaries;
They commonly share, directly or indirectly, profit from the sale of alcoholic beverages; or
They share a common trade name, trademark, logo or theme, or mode of operation identifiable by the public.
